	abstract = {In modern educational environments, efficient time management and accurate student monitoring are critical for enhancing the teaching and learning experience. Traditional methods of attendance recording, such as roll calls or manual sign-in sheets, are time-consuming, error-prone, and vulnerable to misuse through proxy attendance. To address these challenges, this work proposes a real-time automated attendance system that leverages facial recognition and integrates an intelligent analytics dashboard for enhanced monitoring. The system employs Histogram of Oriented Gradients (HOG) with Support Vector Machine (SVM) for face detection, a ResNet-based deep neural network for face embeddings, and Euclidean distance for identity verification. Attendance records are automatically updated in a centralized database, and students marked absent receive instant email notifications. Beyond attendance marking, the proposed system introduces a novel dashboard module that visualizes attendance statistics through interactive charts and reports, including summary distributions, monthly trends, punctuality analysis, and student-wise records. This additional layer of analytics not only improves transparency but also supports administrators and teachers in tracking student engagement and identifying patterns of absenteeism. Experimental deployment demonstrates the system's effectiveness in reducing proxy attendance, saving classroom time, and providing actionable insights through its dashboard interface. © 2025 IEEE.},
