	abstract = {Predicting student achievement in English language learning has traditionally relied on standardized tests and trainer opinions. While these methods provide precious insights, they often fail to capture nuanced components of language talent and character gaining knowledge of desires. Existing techniques commonly contain static checks that don't adapt to the evolving nature of scholar overall performance or provide personalized feedback. This study proposes a singular approach utilizing GPT-3 (Generative Pre-skilled Transformer) models to enhance the prediction of scholar fulfillment in English language learning. GPT-3 models, regarded for their superior natural language processing skills, provide a dynamic and personalized evaluation of scholar texts. Unlike traditional methods, GPT-three can compare complex language capabilities, including grammar, vocabulary utilization, and coherence, and generate tailored remarks that addresses precise areas of development. The methodology entails amassing a various dataset of scholar-written texts and engagement metrics. These data are preprocessed and used to high-quality-song a GPT-three version, allowing it to assess language talent and predict destiny performance. The satisfactory-tuned version analyzes student submissions, generates personalized feedback, and predicts fulfillment primarily based on found styles and contextual know-how. Results exhibit that the GPT-3 based approach substantially improves the accuracy of fulfillment predictions and offers greater actionable feedback as compared to conventional methods. The version's potential to generate real-time, contextually relevant remarks complements the gaining knowledge of revel in by using addressing man or woman wishes and adapting to student progress.  © 2024 IEEE.},
