	abstract = {The aim of this study is to explore the effects of gamification teaching methods on adult undergraduates' academic achievement in a Chinese Literature course. It integrates four poetry game mobile apps, Poetry Challenge, K Poetry for All, Poetry Match, and Classical Poetry Relay into poetry learning and proposes models and strategies for teaching activities based on the ADDIE model. A quasi-experimental research design with pre-test and post-test was adopted. The study involved 80 adult undergraduates, equally divided into an experimental group and a control group. The experimental group participated in a gamified teaching approach, while the control group was taught using traditional methods over a eight-week period. The data were analyzed using mean, independent T-test sample (t = -2.199, p < 0.05) and ANCOVA Results (F=31.414,p=.000) indicate that the gamification teaching method significantly improved students' academic achievement compared to the traditional method in the basic knowledge, but not significantly in the reading comprehension (t =-0.053, p >0.05) and literature writing (t = -1.365, p >0.05). These findings suggest that gamification teaching methods provide a more effective and engaging approach for adult learners in a Chinese Literature course.  © 2025 IEEE.},
