	affiliations = {V.S.B. Engineering College, Department of Information Technology, Karur, India},
	abstract = {The increasing complexity of academic administration necessitates intelligent automation for Department Management Systems (DMS). Traditional systems rely on manual scheduling, attendance tracking, and student evaluation, which results in inefficiencies, scheduling conflicts, and a lack of real-time analytics. Current solutions lack AI-driven predictive insights, automated timetable generation, biometric-based attendance tracking, and intelligent student performance assessments, which are essential for improving institutional efficiency. This research introduces an AI-powered Department Management System (DMS) integrating machine learning (ML), deep learning, and Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) to automate faculty scheduling, optimize student evaluations, and enhance institutional decision-making. The proposed system includes AI-based Timetable Scheduling, Automated Attendance Tracking using biometric authentication, AI-powered Question Paper Generation, and placement shortlisting with AI-driven resume screening. Additionally, a secure role-based authentication framework ensures data privacy and access control across different user levels. Experimental results demonstrate a 15% reduction in scheduling conflicts, 30% improvement in faculty workload balancing, and 96% accuracy in student performance predictions. Comparative evaluations highlight that the AI-powered model outperforms traditional methods in execution speed, resource utilization, and scalability. The proposed framework reduces administrative workload, improves student engagement, and optimizes placement opportunities. Future enhancements will focus on blockchain-integrated academic records, adaptive AI-based learning analytics, and cloud-based deployment for multi-institutional scalability. By leveraging AI and predictive analytics, this system transforms academic management, ensuring efficiency, accuracy, and automation in higher education institutions.  © 2025 IEEE.},
